Analysis: We inspected metrics, traces, and logs for the incident window 2022-03-21 04:00–04:30+08. What has been done and derived: 
- Preprocessing and global-threshold (P95/P5) calculation were done per component-KPI using full series. 
- Metric-level anomaly detection found many container.network KPIs containing 'container.node-5.container_network.*' with consecutive anomalous segments (>=2 minutes) beginning at or shortly after 2022-03-21T04:00:00+08:00 across many different cmdb_id pods. Several of these segments show large breach ratios (e.g., >50%). 
- Trace analysis showed frontends experienced latency spikes and row_count drops starting at ~04:00+08. 
- error_logs show frontends repeatedly logged 'severity: warning, message: failed to retrieve ads' throughout the window starting at the beginning of the window. 
- adservice metrics show only very small, short-magnitude deviations (minor breach ratios) later in the window (~04:03 onward and small JVM GC blips at ~04:28), insufficient in magnitude to explain the widespread frontend symptoms. 
- Many different pod metrics on the same underlying node (node-5) are abnormal — this indicates a node-level network problem affecting all containers scheduled on node-5 rather than a single service. 
Therefore the predominant and earliest sustained fault is network-related anomalies on node-5 observed from 04:00+08 onward. These network anomalies (packet/throughput irregularities) align with frontends' inability to retrieve ads. The magnitude and breadth of the node-5 network KPI breaches (>50% in many cases) make node-level network faults the most plausible root cause rather than isolated adservice performance issues.
Instruction: Root cause summary:
- Root cause component: node-5
- Root cause occurrence datetime (first observed): 2022-03-21T04:00:00+08:00
- Root cause reason: container packet loss / node network issue (manifested as widespread container.network anomalies on node-5, e.g., increased packet/MB, packet drops and errors)

Evidence (concise):
- Multiple container.network KPIs containing 'container.node-5.container_network.*' show consecutive anomalies (>=2 minutes) starting at ~04:00+08 across many pods (high breach ratios in several series).
- Traces from frontends show latency spikes and row_count drops beginning at ~04:00+08, coincident with when node-5 network anomalies begin.
- Frontend error_logs repeatedly report 'failed to retrieve ads' throughout the window, consistent with network connectivity/packet loss to adservice pods.
- adservice metric deviations are minor in magnitude and occur later, consistent with being downstream/secondary symptoms.

Recommendation: treat node-5 network fault (packet loss) as the root cause; actions: investigate node-5 network interface (eth0) for packet drops/errors, check host network stack, CNI, switch connectivity or virtualization host, and consider moving affected pods off node-5 or evicting/cordoning node-5 until network fault is resolved.
